    "text": "Two contributors stand out, led by respiration. Your respiratory rate is 16.6 breaths per minute, above your 30-day average of 15.1 — a shift that often lines up with a body working on something: early illness, alcohol, a heavy evening session like yesterday's 48-minute strength workout, or just a warm room. HRV moved the same direction: your HRV is 58 ms, below your 30-day average of 62.4 ms. Your resting heart rate barely moved — it's 57 bpm, close to your 30-day average of 56.1 bpm — which argues against anything dramatic. One night of this is a note, not a verdict. Tonight's lever: skip intensity, hydrate, and get a full night; if breathing rate stays elevated tomorrow with HRV still low, take an easy day and reassess.",
